<br>
::His eyes glow a bit purple, irritated::  &quot;If you do not learn to hold your tongue boy and think before you speak, you may insult somebody far more powerful than yourself.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades knew quite well, the ONLY people who could match him in power or possibly even overpower him are his two brother Zeus and Poseidon.  With that Hades walked over to the freshly cut human corpse and ran his finger along the open wound, taking some of its blood on his finger.  He then licked his finger, tasting the blood::<br>
<br>
::He looked at the spilled bowl and shook his head looking at Eris:: &quot;It greatly offends me when a god does not know his place.  You do not walk into another god's temple and defile it, or insult them.&quot;<br>
